    "created_at": "2016-07-19T07:41:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-19T08:11:37Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The desync in #11660 isn't caused by SharedRandom.  SharedRandom is simply the first piece of `[Sync]`ed world state that the diverged game flow touches.  Removing these without understanding the actual desync will just push the bug to an even harder to reproduce corner of the engine.\n\nIt would be very unwise to change the smudge code before we have a good understanding on why the remove case desyncs.\n"
  },
