    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@obrakmann and @abcdefg30's testing appears to have isolated the desync to the scorch removals.  This is not an irrelevant piece, and there is no perf difference between the shared and synced randoms.  The scorch code was intentionally using synced random and sync-safe code so that we can have cross-client consistency when somebody finally decides to implement multicell craters.\n"
